上海援鄂医疗队：我们不能治好肺炎就不管了。
Shanghai medical team: We can't cure pneumonia.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
澎湃新闻记者 李佳蔚郁斐 制图进驻武汉第一天，上海医疗队就知道，要治愈的不仅是患者身体，治愈出院也不会是服务终点。
On the first day of her arrival in Wuhan, the Shanghai medical team knew that it was not only the patient's body that should be cured.
时至今日，事实证明他们做得不赖。
To this day, they have proved to be doing well.
2月7日，上海中山医院第四批医疗队进驻武汉大学人民医院东院，整建制接管两个病区（20和22病区，共80张床位），收治的均为重症及危重患者。
On February 7, the fourth medical team from Zhongshan Hospital in Shanghai entered the East Hospital of the People's Hospital of Wuhan University.
截至2月21日，短短两个星期全力救治，70余名重症以上患者已有30多人转为轻症，数量接近一半。
As of February 21, just over two weeks of intensive care, more than 70 patients with severe illness have been turned into mild cases, nearly half of the number.
87岁音乐学院教授的沉默刚到武汉时的情景，医疗队队员、消化科医生李锋清晰记得。
87-year-old music college professor of silence just arrived in Wuhan scene, medical team members, digestive doctor Li Feng clearly remember.
他们去的两个病区，原来是心内科病房，临时改建而成ICU，医疗队着手配齐了必需的医疗设施，分门别类归置。
They went to two areas, the heart of the medical ward, temporarily converted into ICU, the medical team set out to complete the necessary medical facilities, categorize.
病房各区域的医疗、护理、用药等各项管理流程被重新建构。
The management processes of medical treatment, nursing and medication in the ward areas were reorganized.
护士长潘文彦有二十余年重症病房护理经验，她知道一个朴素的道理，“抢救时，医生说要插管，护士就要随时能拿出需要的东西，不能有一分一秒耽误”。
Head nurse Pan Wenyan has more than 20 years of intensive care experience, she knows a simple truth, "When rescue, doctors said to intubate, nurses should be ready to take out what they need, there can be no minute delay."
病房条件改善，但病人的状态令医护人员忧心忡忡。
Conditions in the ward improved, but the patient's condition worried the staff.
有一名87岁的老先生，总是沉默地躺在病床上。
There was an 87-year-old man, always lying in his bed in silence.
每次李锋进去查房，都看到发给他的食物原封不动地放在桌上。
Every time Li Feng entered the room, he saw the food given to him lying untouched on the table.
老先生原是音乐学院教授，因新冠肺炎住院已40多天。
The old gentleman was a professor at the Conservatory of Music and had been hospitalized with Newcastle pneumonia for over 40 days.
他不爱说话，有时盐水吊完也不打铃通知护士。
He was not talkative, and sometimes the saltwater hung up without ringing the nurse.
在武汉大学人民医院东院重症病房，上海医疗队护士喂87岁老先生喝粥。
In Wuhan University People's Hospital East Hospital intensive care ward, Shanghai medical team nurses feed 87-year-old gentleman porridge.
本文图片均由受访者提供这不是孤例。
The photos in this article are provided by the respondents.
武汉不少重症病房存在着类似令人担忧的状况，他们大多是老年人，常见家族集聚式感染，在医院内心失落，担心和思念家人。
Wuhan, a number of severe hospital wards have a similar worrying situation, they are mostly elderly, common familial infection, lost in the hospital heart, worried and missing their families.
“当我们进去问‘你们好吗’，他们都比较漠然地看着我们。
"When we went in and asked, 'How are you', they looked at us rather indifferently.
”这种情况医护人员虽然始料未及，可细想之下，又觉酸楚。
"The doctors and nurses, though not expecting it, felt bitter after thinking about it.
有个病人跟医生讲，除了自己，她先生、女儿相继染病住院，只有女婿和外孙还在外面隔离。
One patient told the doctor that apart from herself, her husband and daughter had been hospitalized, and only her son-in-law and grandson were still isolated.
她很担心他们。
She was worried about them.
在武汉大学人民医院东院重症病房，上海医护人员与患者在病房交流。
In the intensive care ward of the East Hospital of Wuhan University, Shanghai medical staff communicated with patients in the ward.
一条指令：去和每一位患者交谈李锋把自己了解的情况第一时间反映上去，其他医生和护士亦有相关报告。
One of the instructions: to talk to each patient Li Feng to their knowledge of the first time to reflect the situation, other doctors and nurses also have relevant reports.
随即，上海医疗队发出一条指令：医护人员在保障自身防护绝对安全的同时，查房时尽量在病房多停留一会，去和每一位患者交谈，尤其是年纪大的患者。
Immediately, the Shanghai medical team issued a directive that medical staff, while ensuring the absolute safety of their own protection, stay in the ward for as long as possible to talk to each patient, especially the elderly.
与此同时，橘子、苹果、各类营养品被医护人员分送到每个病人手中。
Meanwhile, oranges, apples, and nutrients were distributed to each patient by health workers.
有些患者的亲属因各种原因无法对其照应，医疗队出面，为他们配齐一应生活用品。
Some of the patients' relatives were unable to attend to them for various reasons, and the medical team intervened to provide them with adequate supplies.
这些东西谈不上贵重，但病人拿到时都很开心。
These things were not expensive, but the patients were happy when they got them.
医生和护士也感觉到，清冷的病房逐渐温暖。
Doctors and nurses also felt the warmth of the cold ward.
有一天，李锋和医疗队队长罗哲下去查房，走到前文提及的87岁老先生病床前。
One day, Li Feng and the medical team captain Luozhe went down to check room, went to the above-mentioned 87-year-old man bed.
罗哲询问他近两天好不好，身体有没有不舒服。
Rozhe asked him if he had been feeling well for the past two days.
老先生只说了一句话：“我想回家。
"The old man only said," I want to go home.
”医生理解老先生想回家的心情，但当他说出这句话，两位医生都察觉暗含的意思——老人恐怕想要放弃。
"The doctor understood the old man's desire to go home, but when he said this, both doctors realized the implication - the old man was afraid he wanted to give up.
罗哲没有正面回答老先生的请求，而是问道：“老先生，您原来在乐队是不是指挥家？”老先生抬起头，眼神亮起来。
Instead of answering the old gentleman's request head-on, he asked, "Sir, were you a conductor in the orchestra?" The old gentleman looked up with his eyes bright.
“不是，我不是指挥家，我演奏乐器，吹乐器的。
"No, I'm not a conductor. I play an instrument, I play an instrument.
”“你现在的状态，吹乐器肯定吹不动，”罗哲看到老先生精神一振，继续说，“等你身体再好一点，回去再演奏乐器。
"You can't play an instrument in your present form," continued Roche, seeing the old gentleman's spirit quicken, "when you are better, and go back to playing an instrument.
”简简单单一番对话，老先生轻松了。
"The conversation was brief and the old gentleman relaxed.
打那以后，医生和护士每次进到病房，都和老先生攀谈一会家人的近况，他渐渐打开心扉，治疗中身体有何种反应、有哪里不适，都一五一十地及时告知医护，医生根据情况及时调整治疗方案。
After that, every time the doctor and nurse entered the ward, they talked with the old man about the family for a while. He gradually opened up his heart and told the doctor exactly how the body reacted and what was wrong during the treatment.
他的孩子很关心父亲，常来电话，医生则及时把病情通报到家属。
His child is very concerned about his father, often called, the doctor timely to inform the family.
这些天来，老先生病情不断转好。
The old gentleman has been getting better these days.
他开始主动进食，吃水果和营养液。
He began to eat on his own initiative, eating fruits and nutrients.
临床上，原有气急和缺氧状况均已得到明显改善。
Clinically, the original state of emergency and anoxia has been significantly improved.
更可喜的是，胸部CT和血液指标显示，他的病情正在全面改善。
More encouragingly, the chest CT and blood indicators showed that his condition was improving across the board.
“我们不能说治好肺炎就不管了”截至目前，新冠肺炎是没有特效药的。
"We can't say that curing pneumonia doesn't matter." So far, there is no specific cure for pneumonia.
上海医疗队诊疗的核心是多学科综合治疗。
The core of the diagnosis and treatment of Shanghai medical team is multidisciplinary treatment.
从治愈者的经验看，增加自身免疫力非常重要，这与患者心情放松、饮食作息密切相关。
From the experience of the healer, it is very important to increase one's immunity, which is closely related to the patient's relaxed mood and diet.
经过多日来磨合，医护之间配合得越来越得心应手，医疗、护理已做得更加全面。
After many days of wear and tear, the coordination between the medical care more and more comfortable, medical, nursing has been done more comprehensive.
有一名重症病人神志不清，医生每天要安排高流量氧气，护士则定时去给患者更换纸尿布、擦拭身体、翻身。
One critically ill patient is delirious. Doctors arrange high-flow oxygen every day, and nurses regularly change diapers, wipe the body and turn over.
医生还为患者下了胃管，注射营养物质。
The doctor also gave the patient a stomach tube and an injection of nutrients.
“治愈一个患者不单单是医疗救治，方方面面都在支持。
"Healing a patient is not just about medical care, it's all about support.
”李锋说。
'said Li Feng.
每名患者大约5天做一次全面评估，医生要观察患者胸闷、气急等症状是否改善，通过胸部CT、血液检查，分析影像学指标情况，判断炎症是否吸收。
Each patient underwent a comprehensive assessment about 5 days, the doctor to observe whether the chest tightness, shortness of breath and other symptoms improved, through chest CT, blood tests, analysis of imaging indicators, to determine whether inflammation absorption.
同时，患者食欲、睡眠情况亦是关注的重点。
At the same time, patients appetite, sleep is also the focus of attention.
一个患者一套方案，每次治疗后，医生们聚在一起总结经验，在后续病例中寻求可改进之处。
One patient package, after each treatment, doctors gather to learn lessons and look for improvements in follow-up cases.
现在两个病区，已有30余名重症患者已转为轻症，一些患者即将治愈出院。
Now more than 30 patients in the two affected areas have been turned into mild cases, and some are about to be cured.
不过，医疗队的服务并不止于此。
However, the services of medical teams do not stop there.
有一名75岁新冠肺炎患者伴有肾功能问题。
A 75-year-old man with Newly Coronary Pneumonia had kidney problems.
在他整个治疗过程中，上海医疗队和武汉当地医院联系，请医生进入病房定期为这名患者做血透，保障他的肾功能。
Throughout his treatment, the Shanghai medical team contacted the local Wuhan hospital and asked the doctor to enter the ward to have regular blood transfusions to ensure his kidney function.
在武汉大学人民医院东院，中山医院医疗队部分当班护士合影。
In Wuhan University People's Hospital East Hospital, Zhongshan Hospital part of the nurses on duty.
目前，这个患者的新冠肺炎已经基本治愈，马上要出院。
At present, this patient's new crown pneumonia already basically cured, about to leave hospital.
考虑到他每周两次的血透不能停，医疗队正在为他联系医院，准备出院后的治疗。
Considering that he could not stop bleeding twice a week, the medical team was contacting the hospital to prepare for treatment after his discharge from the hospital.
“我们正在和当地医院联系，想帮这名患者出院后能够稳定地做血透。
"We are in contact with the local hospital to help the patient to have a stable hemodialysis once he is discharged from the hospital.
”李锋说，“我们不能说治好肺炎就不管了。
"We can't say cure for pneumonia.
”戳这里进入“全国新型冠状病毒感染病例实时地图”↓↓↓本期编辑 周玉华推荐阅读。
